She took a breath and blushed, turning a deep red. "Ah, yeah. I think 
that's a good idea. It suddenly feels hot in here." She smiled and 
lowed her head in a shy manner.  She giggled slightly. "I'm sorry, I 
guess I got caught up in the.." She stopped as she looked into his 
eyes. She stared for a moment. She shook her head as if o clear it.
"Yeah, walk, right." She took a step and wrapped her arm around his.
"Good idea, a little fresh air would be good about now."
She smiled and kissed him on the cheek. "Lead the way."
